        <mxCell id="yEVexKfB1VVprKKpYjTD-3" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Flow&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. user using the client app to initiate a request&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Client sending api request with the prompt, system instructions, auth token, model name&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. This goes throw a load balancer into one of our api gateway services - this will handle auth, rate limits&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Request router will handle the tier and prioritization and will enqueue the prompt tho the right Q for prioritization&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. Scheduler/Orchestrator - Pick requests from Q, assign to gpu worker with available capacity&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. GPU workers&amp;nbsp; - running the inference engines push responses to response Qs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;6. Publisher handling ws with clients, has some mapping of the request ID socket and get the right stored connection and stream response back&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
